Arsenal 0-2 Bayern Munich: Referee killed the game - Arsene Wenger
Media playback is not supported on this deviceArsenal boss Arsene Wenger says Italian referee Nicola Rizzoli "killed the game" after his sidelost 2-0 to Bayern Munichin the first leg of their last-16 Champions League tie.Gunners keeper Wojciech Szczesny was sent off in the first half after bringing down Bayern's Arjen Robben, with David Alaba missing the resulting spot kick. Mesut Ozil had missed an earlier penalty for ArsenalThe defending champions made their extra man count after the break, enjoying 88% possession in the second half, as goals from Toni Kroos and Thomas Muller secured the win.